{"_type":"issue","id":"clojure-lora-trainer-c3d","title":"Rework miner to IQuest-style code-flow triplets","description":"Adopt the IQuest-Coder git-history recipe (Tech Report 3.1): (1) lifecycle windowing — sample commits from the 40-80% percentile of project life (mature/stable phase) instead of the most-recent N from HEAD; (2) multi-iteration (R_old, P, R_new) triplets via forward-search spans rather than single-commit before/after; (3) endpoint quality filtering (non-empty Clojure diff, meaningful combined message). Keeps the existing output schema; format change (drop fabricated REPL blocks) tracked separately.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","assignee":"Yogthos","owner":"yogthos@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-06-20T00:07:02Z","created_by":"Yogthos","updated_at":"2026-06-20T00:07:26Z","started_at":"2026-06-20T00:07:26Z","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"clojure-lora-trainer-duq","title":"DeepSeekProvider doubles /v1 in endpoint URL -\u003e 404","description":"deepseek.py built the endpoint as base_url + '/v1/chat/completions'. The synthetic pipeline's setup_llm passed base_url=https://api.deepseek.com/v1, producing .../v1/v1/chat/completions and a 404, so the synthetic generator could not call DeepSeek at all. Normalize base_url (strip trailing /v1) and fix the script default.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"yogthos@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-06-19T23:34:30Z","created_by":"Yogthos","updated_at":"2026-06-19T23:34:39Z","closed_at":"2026-06-19T23:34:39Z","close_reason":"Closed","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"clojure-lora-trainer-nwi","title":"Assembler has no max-length filter; 1.2MB inputs reach training set","description":"The codeflow assembly pipeline (load -\u003e dedup -\u003e balance -\u003e format -\u003e validate) never filters records by length. A full mine of the 22 repos yields inputs up to 1.2MB (~300K tokens) and 232/511 records over 30KB at --max-per-type 150. These blow past any training context window and get silently truncated, wasting the example. Add a max-length drop (or truncation) step in assemble_dataset, configurable via CLI (e.g. --max-input-chars). The validator already scores records but does not drop them.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"Yogthos","owner":"yogthos@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-06-19T23:07:38Z","created_by":"Yogthos","updated_at":"2026-06-19T23:25:51Z","started_at":"2026-06-19T23:22:47Z","closed_at":"2026-06-19T23:25:51Z","close_reason":"Closed","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
